class Solution {
    public int countBinarySubstrings(String s) {
        int prev = 0, curr = 1, res = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == s.charAt(i - 1)) {
                curr++;
            } else {
                res += Math.min(prev, curr);
                prev = curr;
                curr = 1;
            }
        }
        res += Math.min(prev, curr);
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass counts consecutive runs of 0s and 1s; each transition contributes min(prevRun, currRun) valid substrings. Constant space, linear time, minimal energy use.

